+      "canonical_answer": "A race condition occurs when multiple threads access shared mutable state and the result depends on their timing. Operations that look simple, such as count++, are read-modify-write sequences and are not automatically atomic. A synchronized method or block allows only one thread at a time to execute the protected critical section using the same monitor, and it also establishes memory-visibility guarantees. The lock must cover every operation that participates in the invariant.",
