+      "canonical_answer": "ExecutorService separates task submission from thread management. A thread pool can reuse a bounded number of worker threads, limit resource consumption, queue work, and return Future objects for results or failures. Call shutdown() to reject new tasks while allowing submitted tasks to finish, then await termination when the application must wait. If graceful shutdown fails, shutdownNow() can request interruption, but tasks must cooperate with interruption.",
